<Action id="45174" issue="28043" author="aambati" type="comment" created="2018-05-26 21:20:48.0" updateauthor="aambati" updated="2018-05-26 21:20:59.0"> <body><! CDATA  ~nnao After thinking about this problem some more, I think best way to handle this problem with out breaking existing behavior is to print a warning message when user specified CA certificate is not found, if the name and path of the specified cert does not match defaults. For example,  if user specified cert file is /tmp/ca-cert.pem or <serverhome>/myca-cert.pem and file does not exist a warning message is printed.  But if the specified file is <serverHome>ca-cer.pem then no warning message is printed as the server won't be able to distinguish between user supplied vs default cert.  ></body> </Action>
